sql:
SELECT SUM(approved_amount) AS total_approved_amount
FROM loan_applications
WHERE disbursement_date BETWEEN '2023-04-01' AND '2023-04-30';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_approved_applications
FROM loan_applications
WHERE status = 'approved';

external_knowledge:
- "Garden of loan applications" refers to the dataset of loan applications;
- "Flowers" are the loan applications;
- "Tended to" and "watered" refer to the review process;
- "More than once" indicates that the application has been reviewed more than one time.

sql:
SELECT AVG(la.approved_amount) AS overall_average_approved_loan_amount
FROM loan_applications la
JOIN applicants a ON la.applicant_id = a.applicant_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Blossomed with the most approved funds" refers to the highest total approved amount of loans;
- "Largest number of applications" refers to the highest total number of loan applications;
- "Unique applicants" refers to distinct individuals who have applied for loans.

- 'Senior Loan Officer' is a job title indicating a higher level of experience or authority in the loan processing hierarchy;
- The average approved amount is calculated only for applications reviewed and approved by senior loan officers;
- The query limits the results to the top 10 applicants with the highest approved amounts.

- 'pending' and 'approved' statuses refer to the current status of the loan application;
- 'pending' review status indicates that the application is under review;
- 'approved amount' is the amount of credit that has been approved for the loan.

- "reviewed by at least two loan officers" means that the application has been assessed by a minimum of two distinct loan officers;
- "top five applications" refers to the applications with the highest risk scores within each group of loan purpose and type;
- "risk score" is a metric used to evaluate the likelihood of a loan being repaid.

- 'Top 5' refers to the highest approved amounts for each loan officer and purpose;
- 'Last three months' is calculated from the current date;
- 'Purpose' and 'loan officer' are used to group the results.

- 'approved applications' refers to applications with a status of 'approved';
- 'disbursed' means the loan amount has been released to the applicant;
- 'interest rate less than 10%' is a condition applied to filter the applications.

- 'approved loans' refers to loan applications with a status of 'approved';
- 'approved amount between 5000 and 10,000' means the loan amount is within this range;
- 'reviewed more than once' means the loan application has more than one review entry.

- 'Pending' status indicates the application is under review and has not been approved or rejected yet;
- 'High risk score' typically means a score greater than 500, indicating a higher risk of default;
- 'Multiple reviews' means more than one review has been conducted on the application.

- "Cumulative number of approved loan applications" refers to the total number of approved applications over time for each job type;
- "Most recent" indicates the latest date in the dataset;
- "Highest cumulative number" means the job type with the largest total of approved applications as of the most recent date.

- "Financial garden" refers to the financial institution where loan officers handle loan applications;
- "Generous in granting loans" refers to loan officers who have approved a higher average loan amount;
- "Last four months" refers to the period from the start of the current month to the start of the month three months ago;
- "Cumulative approved amount for the most recent month" refers to the total approved loan amount for each loan officer up to the most recent month.
